# Shared .dockerignore for both server + web Dockerfiles (build context =
# repo root). Anything excluded here doesn't get sent to BuildKit, which
# both shrinks the context and avoids accidentally embedding dev state /
# secrets into the image.

# --- VCS ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Python caches / venvs / artifacts ---
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info
.venv
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
.coverage
htmlcov
dist
build

# --- Node / Next caches (web pulls a different ignore set, but excluding
#     these globally is safe — neither image needs them) ---
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/out
**/storybook-static
**/.pnpm-store

# --- Local dev / runtime state (NEVER ship to an image) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.run
secrets

# --- Docs / IDE / OS noise ---
docs
site
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log

# --- Tests (not needed at runtime; tests use testcontainers anyway) ---
tests
**/tests
**/test_*.py

# --- The other service's source (excluded per-image via the explicit
#     COPY allowlist in each Dockerfile, but kept out of the context too) ---
# Server Dockerfile only copies etl_plugins/ + services/anyduct-server/.
# Web Dockerfile only copies services/anyduct-web/ + pnpm workspace files.

# --- Docker / compose files don't need to ship inside the image ---
**/Dockerfile*
**/docker-compose*.yml
docker/
